race.comment: CAPTAIN FENKEL (1) was nudged out at Eagle Farm in stronger before the spell over 1800m and resumed there is a 70 over 1400m and needed the outing. Proven second-up and has the inside barrier and handy 3kg claim. The step up in trip suits, and he's well placed to win. BENFICA LASS (4) was well back on straightening at Toowoomba but finished off well over 1300m. The step up in distance should suit this time around and she can run into the finish. MADALSA (3) was quickly back on track last start, finishing a close third over 1625m at Toowoomba. Tumbles in weight this grade and that brings her right into it. REGGIE'S FOLLY (7) has been in the market at his last couple of starts but hasn't made an impression, last start running fourth at Gatton. Rates as a place chance.
